                    <span>In most countries, DDT was banned only for agricultural use, NOT for control of malaria, in fact it is still widely used today for that purpose. Of course this isn't a long term solution, because of the resistance problem, as Carson foretold all those years ago.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">DONT LISTEN TO BAD REVIEWS</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
